quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
35,19,"The blind and the seeing are not alike,"
35,20,"nor darkness and light;"
35,21,"nor cool shade and torrid heat;"
35,22,"nor are the living and the dead alike. {1} Allah makes to hear whomsoever He wishes, but you, (O Prophet), cannot cause to hear those who are in their graves. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
35,23,"You are no more than a warner. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
35,24,"We have sent you with the Truth to proclaim good news and to warn. Never has there been a nation but a warner came to it. {1}",footnotes:1:That there has been no community in the world for whose guidance Allah did not appoint the Prophets. This has been stated at several places in the Quran. In (Surah Ar- Raad
35,25,"If they give the lie to you now, those that went before them also gave the lie to their Messengers when they came to them with Clear Proofs, {1} with Scriptures, and with the Illuminating Book. {2}",footnotes:1:“Clear proofs”: Proofs which clearly testified that they were Allah’s Messengers.|180598:“Scriptures” probably consisted of good counsels and moral precepts and “the Book” comprised a complete code of the law.
35,26,"Then I seized those who denied the Truth, and how terrible was My punishment!"
35,27,"Do you not see that Allah sent down water from the sky with which We brought forth fruits of diverse hues? In the mountains there are white and red, of diverse hues, and pitchy black;"
35,28,"and human beings too, and beasts, and cattle � diverse are their hues. {1} From among His servants, it is only those who know that fear Allah. {2} Verily Allah is Most Mighty, Most Forgiving. {3}",footnotes:1:This is meant to impress that in the universe created by Allah nowhere is there homogeneity and uniformity; there is variety everywhere. From the same earth and by the same water different kinds of trees are appearing. Even the two pieces of the fruit of the same tree are not uniform in color and size and taste. In the same mountain one will see a variety of colors and a great difference in the material composition of its different parts. Even among human beings and animals one will not see two offspring of the same parents exactly alike. If a person seeks uniformity of the temperaments and dispositions and mentalities in this universe and is bewildered at the differences which have been alluded to in( verses 19-22) above
35,29,"Surely those who recite the Book of Allah and establish Prayer and spend, privately and publicly, out of what We have provided them, look forward to a trade that shall suffer no loss;"
35,30,"(a trade in which they have invested their all) so that Allah may pay them their wages in full and may add to them out of His Bounty. {1} He is Most Forgiving, Most Appreciative. {2}",footnotes:1:This kind of conduct and practice of the believers has been likened to a trade bargain because in trade a man invests his money and labor and capabilities in the hope that he will not only get his capital back and his wages for the time and energy spent but in addition some profit as well. Likewise
